node.text:
What THOUGHTS are you telling yourself when it comes to food? 💭⁣
⁣
When finding advice on weight-loss, the internet is saturated with contradicting information 🙄I vividly remember googling how to lose weight, and coming out pretty confused as one source would claim that cutting carbohydrates is the way to go, while another would claim that a high carb low fat diet is the most effective way! 😅⁣
⁣
Such generalized advice, strips nutrition of its context and overlooks ones OVERALL diet. 😫⁣
⁣
🍝 For example: pasta is a carbohydrate but that doesn’t mean you have to avoid it! You may want to be aware of your portion size in relation to your overall diet.⁣
⁣
🍉 Another example is fruit. The amount of times I have heard “ah but lee, fruit has SO much sugar”. I could honestly roll my eyes. Yes, fruit does in fact contain sugar but it also comes with amazing benefits like vitamins, minerals & fiber! Furthermore, food containing sugar is not a problem in itself, instead- the quantity how often you consume other sugar containing foods in your overall diet is most relevant.⁣
⁣
One of the best things I ever did was question such beliefs and ask myself WHY? 🤷‍♀️ Changing my mindset towards food has honestly been life changing and given me so much clarity🙏⁣
Credit: @wholesome_lee

￼REALNESS IN YOUR FEED 💫 

No editing. No smoothing. No posing.

Just relaxing in the sunshine. 

 Remember. Life is a gift that can be taken away in an instant. Try not to sweat the tummy rolls.

💖💫🦋
@karinairby
